data.title: Office Properties Income Trust, based in Newton, Mass., is reducing debt and strengthening balance sheet by entering into a restructuring support agreement with note holders of senior secured notes due September 2029, aiming to substantially deleverage.
data.description: In Newton, Massachusetts, Office Properties Income Trust (OPI) revealed a Restructuring Support Agreement with the September 2029 Ad Hoc Group of senior secured note holders. This agreement aims to restructure the corporate debt of OPI and enable significant deleveraging of its balance sheet. The agreement involves senior secured notes due September 2029. This move is crucial for OPI to improve its financial standing and reduce debt, underscoring a strategic effort to enhance the company's financial health.

data.title: HK regulator ramps up oversight on digital assets to protect investors from risks related to cryptocurrency holdings. #HongKong #regulation #cryptocurrency
data.description: The Securities and Futures Commission (SFC) in Hong Kong has increased monitoring of digital asset treasuries to safeguard investors from potential risks linked to cryptocurrency holdings. This move comes as part of efforts to ensure investor protection and is in response to the growing prominence of digital assets in the financial sector. By focusing on these assets, the SFC aims to enhance oversight and mitigate any associated risks for investors. This heightened scrutiny by the SFC underscores the importance of regulating the digital asset market effectively to safeguard investor interests in a rapidly evolving financial landscape.

data.title: Metallus extends labor contract by 90 days after USW members reject tentative agreement in Canton, Ohio.

data.title: Kohat Uni in Pakistan partners with MindHYVE.ai™ to bring ArthurAI™ for academic transformation.
data.description: In a significant development for higher education in Pakistan, Kohat University of Science & Technology (KUST) based in Kohat has announced a partnership with MindHYVE.ai™ to bring ArthurAI™, a cutting-edge agentic AI learning platform, to its academic programs. This collaboration marks a milestone for KUST and the field of higher education in Pakistan. The initiative is aimed at enhancing the academic experience for students by integrating advanced AI technology into their learning environment. Kohat University of Science & Technology is set to benefit from the innovative capabilities of ArthurAI™ as it strives to provide a modern and efficient educational experience. This partnership signifies a crucial step towards the digital transformation of education in Pakistan, highlighting the university's commitment to staying at the forefront of technological advancements.

data.title: Carbon Capture Materials Market to reach $99,098.5 million by 2030, due to demand from high-emission industries. Membranes and alkaline solvents key materials, with post-combustion capture reducing up to 90% of CO2. Regulatory pressures and carbon markets drive demand. Market poised for growth with stricter emission limits globally.
data.description: The Carbon Capture Materials Market is expected to grow from USD 66,904.7 million in 2025 to USD 99,098.5 million by 2030 at a CAGR of 8.2%. Industries like cement, steel, and chemicals aiming to decarbonize are driving the demand for carbon capture materials. CCS systems, like membranes and alkaline solvents, help in reducing CO2 emissions up to 90%. Stricter emission regulations in Europe and North America are prompting industries to adopt CCS, boosting the market for capture materials. Key players in the market include Ecolab, BASF, DOW, and Mitsubishi Heavy Industries. Membranes are expected to dominate the material segment, and power generation leads in end-use industry segment. Major challenges include high energy requirements and costs for large-scale material regeneration. The study's full details are available on Benzinga.com.
